image.altText: a woman smiles for the camera arm-in-arm with a girl whose face is blurred out

props.synopsis: Cindy White, the daughter of Vyleen White who was stabbed to death in the car park of a Redbank Plains shopping centre, says her mother "loved everybody" and doesn't want her death to divide the community.

title.children: 'I do not want her death to divide Australians': Alleged murder victim Vyleen White's daughter calls for unity

image.altText: Masked delivery driver in a car with a bag of takeaway food.

image.altText: Dutton chuckles as he points at Albanese across the dispatch box

image.altText: Three frames of a woman, the third a jogger.

image.altText: Blurred man in background refuses glass of whiskey

image.altText: A doctor holds a stethoscope in two clasped hands
